    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-chilli-double-chicken-breast-and-garden-veg-noodles/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced chicken </strong>and cook for 6-7 min or until starting to brown</p><p>(Doubled your protein? Use 2 pans!)</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-chilli-double-chicken-breast-and-garden-veg-noodles/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your<strong> medium egg noodles</strong> to a large bowl, cover them with<strong> boiled water</strong> and stir for 10 secs to separate the noodles</p><p>Set aside to soak for 5-6 min</p><p>Drain the<strong> soaked noodles </strong>and reserve 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [100ml]</span> of the <strong>starchy noodle water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-chilli-double-chicken-breast-and-garden-veg-noodles/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-chilli-double-chicken-breast-and-garden-veg-noodles/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken has started to brown, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-chilli-double-chicken-breast-and-garden-veg-noodles/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>soy sauce,</strong> <strong>red chilli relish </strong>and <strong>cornflour </strong>to a small bowl with the <strong>reserved starchy noodle water </strong>and mix until fully combined\u2013 this is your <strong>sweet chilli sauce</strong></p><p>Once softened, add your <strong>garden veg mix </strong>and <strong>soaked noodles </strong>to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-chilli-double-chicken-breast-and-garden-veg-noodles/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>sweet chilli sauce </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until everything is coated in sauce and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>sweet chilli chicken & garden veg noodles</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-chilli-double-chicken-breast-and-garden-veg-noodles/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sweet chilli chicken & garden veg noodles</strong></p><p>Garnish with your <strong>crispy onions</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
